{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"27126f03-793b-4743-96c0-7ad5b925bd65","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, so here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a **dotnet tool**:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n  <!-- Makes it a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Steps to publish\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** is the critical property — without it, `dotnet pack` produces a library package, not a tool.\n- **`ToolCommandName`** controls the CLI command name users type after installing.\n- The project **must** have `OutputType` set to `Exe`.\n- Include a `README.md` in the package via `<None Include=\"README.md\" Pack=\"true\" PackagePath=\"/\" />` for the NuGet listing.\n- For CI, store your NuGet API key as a secret and push from your pipeline.\n\nWant me to scaffold the project with these settings?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"146c205a-7406-41e9-8015-04f09cf430c7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory doesn't exist yet. The user is asking what they need to configure, not asking me to create the project. Let me give them guidance on what's needed to publish a C# MCP server as a dotnet tool to NuGet.org.","outputTokens":597},"id":"5bcf1ee8-2b14-40cf-a0a7-780fb8a5cf1b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:55:47.022Z","parentId":"0350589e-c7be-41d8-ac96-9ffebac45b6f"}
